race.description: 2025 Ladbrokes The Blacks A Fake Queensland Championship (Group 1)
race.comment: Defending champion LEAP TO FAME (10) returns off his New Zealand raid where he was a brave second after a tough run in the New Zealand Cup before landing another Group 1 in the New Zealand Free For All last time out. He's had a lot of travel but this is his backyard and he loves it here, winning 40 of 46 attempts and his lone defeat in eight tries at this distance was a luckless second in this race two years ago. Draws on the back row but knows how to do it tough and win. DON HUGO (4) has yet to win this time in but his last two efforts from back row draws have had merit and he'll be peaking. Has the barrier advantage over LEAP TO FAME and used that to beat him in the Miracle Mile earlier this year. THE JANITOR NZ (12) won three in a row here before a brave Sunshine Sprint effort when he worked but fought well to miss by a head. Tricky draw and the distance is an unknown but he is on the up. Inter Dominion runner-up SPEAK THE TRUTH (5) strikes at 50 per cent fresh and is trialling well.
